values: Okay, so tomorrow i'm leaving for spring break, and i'm very excited. But right now i'm bored to tears! Katie took the tv home with her because it will be in our new house, so i'm stuck here without much to do. Not having a tv really forces you to examine your life. I find that i have no life. I have already done the internet thing - over it. I packed all my books into my car, or else i would be reading one, and i have no movies to watch on my laptop, and i've already watched three buffy episodes. I guess i could clean the dorm (it's really dusty) or do homework (yeah right). So now, i'm just typing this, listening to my suitmates get ready to go out (on a THURSDAY!!), but it's rainy and i'm not in the mood to tolerate a bunch of drunks who have been wasted since 5am. So i'm just complaining instead.

Your brain: 60% interpersonal, 80% visual, 220% verbal, and 40% mathematical!
Congratulations on being 400% smart! Actually, on my test, everyone is. The above score breaks down what kind of thinking you most enjoy doing. A score above 100% means you use that kind of thinking more than average, and a score below 100% means you use it less. It says nothing about how good you are at any one, just how interested you are in each, relatively. A substantial difference in scores between two people means, conclusively, that they are different kinds of thinkers.

Matching Summary: Each of us has different tastes. Still, I offer the following advice, which I think is obvious:

  1. Don't date someone if your interpersonal percentages differ by more than 80%.
  2. Don't be friends with someone if your verbal percentages differ by more than 100%.
  3. Don't have sex with someone if their math percentage is over 200%.

Thanksgiving weekend. What more do i have to say? It was a time of giving thanks (duh). I spent more time with family than ever before. It was insane. And you know what is even more insane? Your aunt telling you that pot and shrooms are ok (because they're natural) but not to do coke. And telling you about her honeymoon to europe (specifically amsterdam) and all the fun that they had there. And driving around your drunk father and stepmom is always a nice way to spend thanksgiving. But don't get me wrong, I had a lot of fun. Family get-togethers on my dad's side are always a blast. My family is like a sitcom, and i like it that way. And my stepdad's family came in from philly, which is always fun times. I got to endure from all sides how much more grown up i was, both in appearance and in behavior. And on the friends front, i didn't get to go to jacobs like i wanted. It was my decision, and i'm kind of regretting it now, but running on two hours of sleep and going clubbin is not an option for me. But i did miss all my friends that i didn't get to see. However, going out to dinner with Anna and seeing ash was fun, and then seeing napoleon dynamite for the 45th time with anna and chels was a blast. I miss everyone so much. I can't wait until break, and i'll have 3 weeks to fool around with everyone. Hopefully next time i'll get to see bev! and adrienne, and everyone else. I hope thanksgiving was good times for all.

ok, so my week has been crazy. My computer wasn't working earlier, but now it's ok

i've cried this week; thursday was officially one of the craziest days (emotionally-wise) that i've had in a long time.
I cried [a lot], and i talked to people from home about various things, which put me in a better mood, and kt and matt and i stayed up really late and watched how to deal and we talked until about 2 in the morning which was really awesome, then i had to wake up at 7. I was not a happy camper in the morning.

Yesterday (friday), my mom and my grandma came up for a little bit, and we saw the Miami University Symphony Orchestra. There was a song performed by global rhythms, and it was so completely and utterly awesome, the rest was just mediocre. And then we went to see the a capella groups on campus: the cheezies and remnants (boys) and the misfitz (girls). they were all awesome, but i really like the remnants the best. They sounded great, and get really into it. I want their cd. And then I came back to the dorm and sarah, matt, kt and i watched Office Space. It was so hilarious. i definitely understand why everyone who sees it loves it.

And today we woke up and went to the $6 China Buffet with tara, matt, and sarah. It was a lot of fun. we then watched pirates of the carribbean. And then we saw the notebook, and we all shed a little tear. Late night wendy's is a good idea - frosties and french [freedom] fries are great. Also great, star gazing. shooting stars are the coolest, and it's just a neat feeling. 

So overall, a good time. I'm pretty happy here, except for the fleeting feelings of inadequacy. But i have some really good friends here now, and that's all that matters, but i really do miss my friends at home and elsewhere. You guys are awesome and i love you.

All i really wanted to say was that i think i'm finally starting to like it here. and it's about time i quit lying about it to other people because it's finally true. And that's all i think i have to say.

And that's on top of all my reading for those classes. i'm really bogged down right now and feeling stressed. i live for the weekends. and that's the end of this entry. except for i'm getting a hair cut on friday. boogie-woogie!

oi. I'm feeling a lot of mixed emotions right now. I'm so excited and ready for college (aka going away), but i know this week is going to be the last time i see people on a (semi)regular basis. and i'm going to miss a lot of people i didn't know i would. and i'm not going to miss people i thought i would miss. and that's sad. I don't really know what is going on right now in my life, like with anything, and it is almost starting to piss me off. things just keep getting thrown at me, and it's hard to just take a step back and take a deep breath. I really don't want to think about what will happen in the months that i'm not here. i don't want to think about the people i may never see again, and if i did, how weird/akward/amazing(?) it will all be. I don't want to leave my friends that i've had for years and who have always been there for me. I don't want to risk them forgetting about me, and generally having the times of their lives without me (how selfish is that?!)

I won't forget about all the amazing times i've had with every single person that has been my friend. And i'm going to try my hardest to keep in touch with you all. But it goes both ways. Don't go all shannon on me. OR ELSE! 

School is just around the corner. I leave friday morning. Thanks Colin and Alan for helping us move in. I think i'm ready. 

Oh yeah, josh groban was AMAZING!! And we saw lots of people there (Mrs. Ferrell and her sister, Joe Sofranko, and Mrs. Miller). And thanks Laura for coming. you are amazing. and i'm looking forward to you rumpus on sunday.

Wow. shannon's birthday party. that is something. i can't believe that kid is 18. it seems like just yesterday we were in the third grade. all of that's over now. and i feel like i'll probably never see her again. Like that part of my life is finally behind me. But of course, i'll want to see all of my friends who are an active part of my life. you'll always be a part of me. 

so yeah, my big birthday's coming up soon. I'll be 18 on September 9th.
